BusyAge began as a consultancy unit with a clear vision: to bring structured support to professionals and early-stage founders. Over time, as we faced systemic gaps and unstructured chaos in the Indian startup ecosystem, we decided to build a new model — one rooted in roles, not just startups. From SaaS solutions to incubation frameworks, from micro-projects to equity-driven Troups — BusyAge became the testing ground and launchpad for what would later grow into the Ourown Ecosystem. We didn’t just serve clients — we built structures that enabled ownership.